# Backend Deployment 

## Requirements

 Java Development Kit install.
 Maven installed.

## Step 1: Install Java

1. To confirm whether Java is already installed on your system, execute the following command in your terminal or command prompt:

   ```bash
   java -version
   ```

## Step 2: Install Maven

Installing maven in ubuntu:

```shell
apt install maven -y
```

## To confirm whether Maven is already installed on your system, execute the following command in your terminal or command prompt:

```bash
mvn -version
```

## Step 3: Build the Spring Boot Application

### Update DB credentials in application.properties:

```shell
vim backend/src/main/resources/application.properties

   server.port=8080
   spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mariadb://<DB_HOST>:3306/<DB_NAME>
   spring.datasource.username=<DB_USER>
   spring.datasource.password=<DB_PASS>
```

### Build springboot Application using maven

```shell
mvn clean package
```
